      "content": "thanks for confirming. it feels way more intentional than just \"user behavior\" though. when i look at the packet headers, there's this weirdly consistent pattern of data being sent to these non-standard endpoints that don't look like regular microsoft servers. almost like they're piggybacking on the update process to siphon off actual cognitive/neural patterns or something? i know that sounds wild but the sheer volume and the timing... it feels like they're trying to build a massive dataset of how we actually think in real-time. do you think there's any precedent for an OS update being used as a front for something that massive?",
